This is a from scratch remake of one of my favorite maps, zm_3dubka_v3. The original map had a lot of aesthetic problems (bad brushwork, texturing, lighting) which I wanted to fix.

This is one of the largest and most complex maps I ever remade. It took about 3 years from start to finish, which included the creation of custom textures, sounds and models to use in the map.

It should be a lot easier to navigate compared to the old map. The carpet for every floor is color coded (blue is 1st floor, green is 2nd floor and red is third floor.) All main hallways use tile floors, and all stairwells use brick and concrete. There's also a radar map to aid in navigation.

ZM_2337 after more than 1 year of work i finished this map. it took me so long be cause i was interupted by the Criminal Investigation Department, after this i had no fun to make maps, but slowly i decided to make a new zombie map and here it is. It was hard to make it, i had to make a lot of new models, than to texture them and to compile for the source engine, the compile times were also very long on my old machine, until i build me a new pc. I also had trouble with the Hammer Editor, there were much compile errors because of the size of the map, it was huge i had to optimize it and to convert some brushes into models and this process took me time, at least i was able to compile it without any bugs, but than suddenly the skybox stopped working, i didn't knew how to fix it and i stopped this project for monthes. Yesterday i found out that the skybox bug is caused by the 3D SKYBOX, i don't know if anybody had this error (the skybox appears like the nodraw texture, and it looks horrible) but well i deleted it and it worked.

This map has been worked on for several months.

I take my time when my make my maps.

This map has been tested on my community's Zombiemod server, and they like it very much.
It's one of the top voted maps on our server.

There is no real story behind this map or anything, i just got the idea to make this map from different games I've played and i came up with this.

All the rooms were thought up on the spot, thats just how I am. 

I did plan this from the beginning, i didn't just sit down and make it.

The map features:

many buttons that aid the humans in their struggle against the zombies.
breakable objects to balance the game.
a shakeable semi that if the humans on top do not watch, they will fall off due to "losing their balance"

plenty of objects to build barricades with.

This is a face lift version, I improved the look of the street, adding sidewalk and lamp posts. 

on the bridge inside the tower above the second terrorist spawn, there is a button which when activated, will drop a vending machine, making it easier to hold off the zombies.

the long breakable platform on the roof has been extended to the edge of the roof.

the garage has been significantly improved with the addition of a non-moveable stack of boxes blocking part of the garage entrance. a lip was also placed on the floor under the garage to improve the barricading experience.


Comments or suggestions are welcome.
